}}</ref> Brightman was cast in the film at the last minute after the original actress who was cast for the role was dropped.<ref name="sgirls" />

On 8 August 2008, Brightman sang the Olympic theme song, "[[You and Me (Olympic theme song)|You and Me]]", with Chinese star [[Liu Huan]] in both [[Standard Mandarin|Mandarin]] and English at the [[2008 Summer Olympics opening ceremony|Beijing Olympics opening ceremony]]. The performance was broadcast to over five billion viewers. In the 26 hours after the performance, "You and Me" was downloaded 5.7&nbsp;million times.<ref name="StarPulse">{{cite web|url=http://www.starpulse.com/news/index.php/2008/10/18/sarah_brightman_to_release_first_ever_ch_4 |title=Sarah Brightman To Release First Ever Christmas CD, 'A Winter Symphony,' Nov. 4 |publisher=Starpulse.com |access-date=25 July 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news
